    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:1.1",
          "pli": "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:1.2",
          "pli": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:1.3",
          "pli": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants!” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:1.4",
          "pli": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:1.5",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:2.1",
          "pli": "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe … ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:2.2",
          "pli": "ekapuggalassa, bhikkhave, kappaṃ sandhāvato saṃsarato siyā evaṃ mahā aṭṭhikaṅkalo aṭṭhipuñjo aṭṭhirāsi yathāyaṃ vepullo pabbato, sace saṃhārako assa, sambhatañca na vinasseyya. ",
          "en": "One person roaming and transmigrating for an eon would amass a heap of bones the size of this Mount Vepulla, if they were gathered together and not lost. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:2.3",
          "pli": "Taṃ kissa hetu? ",
          "en": "Why is that? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:2.4",
          "pli": "Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe … ",
          "en": "Transmigration has no known beginning. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:2.5",
          "pli": "alaṃ vimuccitun”ti. ",
          "en": "This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:3.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
          "en": "That is what the Buddha said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:3.2",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: ",
          "en": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:4.1",
          "pli": "“Ekassekena kappena, ",
          "en": "“If the bones of a single person "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:4.2",
          "pli": "puggalassaṭṭhisañcayo; ",
          "en": "for a single eon were gathered up, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:4.3",
          "pli": "Siyā pabbatasamo rāsi, ",
          "en": "they’d make a pile the size of a mountain: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:4.4",
          "pli": "iti vuttaṃ mahesinā. ",
          "en": "so said the great hermit. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:5.1",
          "pli": "So kho panāyaṃ akkhāto, ",
          "en": "And this is declared to be "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:5.2",
          "pli": "vepullo pabbato mahā; ",
          "en": "as huge as Mount Vepulla, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:5.3",
          "pli": "Uttaro gijjhakūṭassa, ",
          "en": "higher than the Vulture’s Peak "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:5.4",
          "pli": "magadhānaṃ giribbaje. ",
          "en": "in the Magadhan mountain range. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:6.1",
          "pli": "Yato ca ariyasaccāni, ",
          "en": "But then, with right understanding, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:6.2",
          "pli": "sammappaññāya passati; ",
          "en": "a person sees the noble truths—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:6.3",
          "pli": "Dukkhaṃ dukkhasamuppādaṃ, ",
          "en": "suffering, suffering’s origin, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:6.4",
          "pli": "dukkhassa ca atikkamaṃ; ",
          "en": "suffering’s transcendence, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:6.5",
          "pli": "Ariyaṃ caṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ, ",
          "en": "and the noble eightfold path "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:6.6",
          "pli": "dukkhūpasamagāminaṃ. ",
          "en": "that leads to the stilling of suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:7.1",
          "pli": "Sa sattakkhattuṃparamaṃ, ",
          "en": "After roaming on seven times at most, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:7.2",
          "pli": "sandhāvitvāna puggalo; ",
          "en": "that person "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:7.3",
          "pli": "Dukkhassantakaro hoti, ",
          "en": "makes an end of suffering, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:7.4",
          "pli": "sabbasaṃyojanakkhayā”ti. ",
          "en": "with the ending of all fetters.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:7.5",
          "pli": "Dasamaṃ. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:7.6",
          "pli": "Paṭhamo vaggo. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:8.1",
          "pli": "Tiṇakaṭṭhañca pathavī, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:8.2",
          "pli": "assu khīrañca pabbataṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:8.3",
          "pli": "Sāsapā sāvakā gaṅgā, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn15.10:8.4",
          "pli": "daṇḍo ca puggalena cāti. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
